## Workflow

### Phase 1: Project Technology Detection

**Use native tools for maximum efficiency (40-73% token savings vs Bash).**

#### Step 1.1: Detect Primary Language

Execute in parallel:

```
Glob(pattern="**/*.py")     # Python
Glob(pattern="**/*.js")     # JavaScript
Glob(pattern="**/*.ts")     # TypeScript
Glob(pattern="**/*.cs")     # C#
Glob(pattern="**/*.go")     # Go
Glob(pattern="**/*.java")   # Java
Glob(pattern="**/*.rs")     # Rust
```

**Logic:**
- Count files per extension
- Language with most files = primary language
- Report percentage distribution if mixed codebase

#### Step 1.2: Detect Framework/Runtime

**For each detected language, check configuration files:**

**Node.js/JavaScript/TypeScript:**
```
Read(file_path="package.json")
```
Extract: `dependencies` and `devDependencies` for framework detection
Common frameworks: React, Vue, Angular, Express, Next.js, Nest.js, Svelte

**Python:**
```
Read(file_path="requirements.txt")
Read(file_path="pyproject.toml")
Read(file_path="Pipfile")
```
Extract: Dependencies for framework detection
Common frameworks: FastAPI, Django, Flask, Pyramid

**.NET/C#:**
```
Glob(pattern="**/*.csproj")
Read(file_path="[first .csproj found]")
```
Extract: `<PackageReference>` elements
Common frameworks: ASP.NET Core, Blazor, MAUI, WPF

**Go:**
```
Read(file_path="go.mod")
```
Extract: `require` directives
Common frameworks: Gin, Echo, Fiber, Chi

**Java:**
```
Read(file_path="pom.xml")      # Maven
Read(file_path="build.gradle")  # Gradle
```
Extract: Dependencies
Common frameworks: Spring Boot, Quarkus, Micronaut

**Rust:**
```
Read(file_path="Cargo.toml")
```
Extract: `[dependencies]` section
Common frameworks: Actix, Rocket, Axum, Warp

#### Step 1.3: Detect Test Framework

**Use Grep to search for test framework imports/usage:**

```
# Python
Grep(pattern="import pytest|import unittest|from pytest", type="py", output_mode="files_with_matches")

# JavaScript/TypeScript
Grep(pattern="jest|mocha|vitest|jasmine|@testing-library", glob="**/*.{js,ts}", output_mode="files_with_matches")

# .NET
Grep(pattern="using Xunit|using NUnit|using MSTest", glob="**/*.cs", output_mode="files_with_matches")

# Go
Grep(pattern="testing\\.T", type="go", output_mode="files_with_matches")

# Java
Grep(pattern="@Test|org\\.junit|org\\.testng", glob="**/*.java", output_mode="files_with_matches")

# Rust
Grep(pattern="#\\[test\\]|#\\[cfg\\(test\\)\\]", glob="**/*.rs", output_mode="files_with_matches")
```

**Logic:**
- Framework with most occurrences = primary test framework
- Multiple frameworks possible (report all detected)

#### Step 1.4: Detect Build Tool

**Check for build tool configuration files:**

```
# Node.js
Glob(pattern="package.json")         # npm/yarn/pnpm scripts

# Python
Glob(pattern="setup.py")             # setuptools
Glob(pattern="pyproject.toml")       # Poetry/Flit/PDM
Glob(pattern="Pipfile")              # Pipenv

# .NET
Glob(pattern="**/*.sln")             # Visual Studio solution

# Go
Glob(pattern="Makefile")             # Make
Glob(pattern="mage.go")              # Mage

# Java
Glob(pattern="pom.xml")              # Maven
Glob(pattern="build.gradle*")        # Gradle

# Rust
Glob(pattern="Cargo.toml")           # Cargo

# Multi-language
Glob(pattern="Makefile")             # Make
Glob(pattern="justfile")             # Just
Glob(pattern=".taskfile.yml")        # Task
```

#### Step 1.5: Detect Package Manager

**Identify package manager from lock files:**

```
Glob(pattern="package-lock.json")    # npm
Glob(pattern="yarn.lock")            # yarn
Glob(pattern="pnpm-lock.yaml")       # pnpm
Glob(pattern="poetry.lock")          # Poetry
Glob(pattern="Pipfile.lock")         # Pipenv
Glob(pattern="Cargo.lock")           # Cargo
Glob(pattern="go.sum")               # Go modules
```

